data.title: Cathedral Church of the Holy and Undivided Trinity (Carlisle Cathedral), Carlisle, Cumbria, UK
data.meta_description: Seen from outside the south porch, on the immediate left, with the choir extending right (eastwards) from the tower and crossing. The stonework reminds me of Chester Cathedral; in both cases, the local New Red Sandstone has weathered almost to black in places, particularly the pinnacles and grotesques. Better On Black?
data.text:
Seen from outside the south porch, on the immediate left, with the choir extending right (eastwards) from the tower and crossing.

The stonework reminds me of Chester Cathedral; in both cases, the local New Red Sandstone has weathered almost to black in places, particularly the pinnacles and grotesques.

Better On Black?
